item.title: [+922] Facebook 'Doppelganger' Craze is Illegal
item.description: The doppelgänger meme currently sweeping across Facebook is actually illegal & breaks the Facebook terms of service. If you don't use Facebook (??), or you haven't logged in during the past week, the 'doppelganger' thing is about replacing your profile pic w/ your celebrity look-alike. Harmless, you might think, but the Facebook TOS forbid it.

item.description: Tomorrow will mark three weeks since the massive January 12th earthquake in Haiti, and tent cities remain full, even as some businesses and factories are beginning to reopen in Port-au-Prince. Now that massive amounts of aid have arrived, distribution problems have cropped up and are being addressed.

item.title: [+651] State of the Internet in 2009 (Infographic)
item.description: Here we take a look at exactly who is using the Internet the most, how they are using it and how much the amount of usage is increasing. At a glance, we can see that there are the same number of men and women who use the Internet. However, their age, educational background and level of income may influence how much time they spend online.
